HEADWORD: Proötic
<hw>Pro*⟦oum⟧"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>pro-</ets> + Gr. <?/, <?/, an ear.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>In front of the auditory capsule; -- applied especially to a bone,
or center of ossification, in the periotic capsule.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A prootic bone.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

